It is the basic requirement of metal to be used in initial piercings and for healing. Lots of people are fine to use the basic 316L steel, but for some people with extremely sensitive skin, we suggest getting our top grade of metal Grade 23 titanium ring ( You can find it in the Comparison Products below). reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Quality Ring — When You Get the Correct Size
reviews.reviewText: I purchased two of rings for my nose in two different sizes: 5mm and 6mm. After measuring my piercing, I opted for the 5mm first; had ordered a different brand in 7mm, which was way too large. The 5mm was snug, and in retrospect, too small. I did have trouble with the closure, as it didn’t want to close smoothly. Unfortunately, I had bumped my nose, causing my piercing to swell and become irritated, so the ring had to go. Because it was so snug, I couldn’t get it open; I had to cut it off with wire cutters. Reordered in the 6mm: opened/closed more smoothly than the previous and fit in my nose better. Haven’t taken it out since I purchased months ago, and it’s done very well. Very pleased with the quality for the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great fit, but hard to get in.
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I love this new ring! I hated the ones that always turned and it looked like I had a booger in my nose. This one is sleek, easy to put on and doesn’t stretch out. I think I got too big of a width because it hurt when I poked it through, probably should’ve went with an 18 not a 20 but it works now! I love it! And the price is hard to beat!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I used to use one of the regular hoops that always have a little opening. However, it kept getting stuck in my nose because I couldn’t clamp it shut enough- leading to multiple infections. This is perfect. Easy to put in, easy to close, and easy to take out if needed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice, sturdy nose ring
reviews.reviewText: I actually love love this nose ring! It was really well made. The only thing I don't like about it is how hard it was to open the opening to take it out. My husband literally had to use pliers and then it broke which was really disappointing. If he would not have used pliers we could not have gotten it open. I was actually a little sad because this was one of my favorite nose rings that I've ever had. Great value for the money and I definitely recommend. It would be nice if they could work on it to make it where it's not so hard to open. Also the only other thing I didn't like about it was how thick it was, I like for a nose ring to hug my nose and then this one was just a little too big. I would definitely wear it again though.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars How to put it in
reviews.reviewText: Hard to open and hard to put in and almost impossible to close it but I did it with 2 pairs of cuticle trimmers and finally snapped it into place.. besides that it looks really cute and the material is good so I’ll give it 4 stars… beware put the long side in first because I tried it the other way while it was open and it wouldn’t go in with the little part open going first so just do it with the longest part going in first then snap it into place. Once in you can’t feel it and it becomes very comfortable

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Way too big for my nostril; put in upper cartilage
reviews.reviewText: I showed a pic with flash too so you could see the gold shine. I guess 8mm is too big for my particular nostril but I love how it lays in my upper cartilage. Can move round and round with no seam apparent. Very easy to install even with nails. Ordered some smaller sizes for nose of this style that clicks it’s nice to not have to bend it; the only con with the clickers are that the smallest gauge is 20. With the bend ones you can get 22 or even 24. But still 5 stars! Stays in thru showers and brushing hair and sleeping, very secure. Will update review if it discolors in time.
Me gustó mucho, me ha durado bastante y no mancha
